	</div>

				<div id="bodyContent" class="vector-body ve-init-mw-desktopArticleTarget-targetContainer" aria-labelledby="firstHeading" data-mw-ve-target-container="">
					<div class="vector-body-before-content">
							<div class="mw-indicators">
		</div>

						<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
					</div>
					<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
					
					
					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r1251242444">.mw-parser-output .ambox{border:1px solid #a2a9b1;border-left:10px solid #36c;background-color:#fbfbfb;box-sizing:border-box}.mw-parser-output .ambox+link+.ambox,.mw-parser-output .ambox+link+style+.ambox,.mw-parser-output .ambox+link+link+.ambox,.mw-parser-output .ambox+.mw-empty-elt+link+.ambox,.mw-parser-output .ambox+.mw-empty-elt+link+style+.ambox,.mw-parser-output .ambox+.mw-empty-elt+link+link+.ambox{margin-top:-1px}html body.mediawiki .mw-parser-output .ambox.mbox-small-left{margin:4px 1em 4px .ambox-delete{border-left:10px solid #b32424}.mw-parser-output .ambox-content{border-left:10px solid #f28500}.mw-parser-output .ambox-style{border-left:10px solid #fc3}.mw-parser-output .ambox-move{border-left:10px solid #9932cc}.mw-parser-output .ambox-protection{border-left:10px solid #a2a9b1}.mw-parser-output .ambox .mbox-text{border:none;padding:0.25em 0;text-align:center}.mw-parser-output .ambox .mbox-empty-cell{border:none;padding:0;width:1px}.mw-parser-output .ambox .mbox-image-div{width:52px}@media(min-width:720px){.mw-parser-output .ambox{margin:0 10%}}@media print{body.ns-0 .mw-parser-output .ambox{display:none!important}}</style><table class="box-Very_long plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-style ambox-very_long" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td class="mbox-image"><div class="mbox-image-div"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img alt="" src="List%20of%20subnational%20entities%20by%20Human%20Development%20Index%20-%20Wikipedia_files/Edit-clear.svg_002.webp" decoding="async" width="40" height="40" class="mw-file-element" srcset="List%20of%20subnational%20entities%20by%20Human%20Development%20Index%20-%20Wikipedia_files/Edit-clear.svg.webp 1.5x, List%20of%20subnational%20entities%20by%20Human%20Development%20Index%20-%20Wikipedia_files/Edit-clear.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="48" data-file-height="48"></span></span></div></td><td class="mbox-text"><div class="mbox-text-span">This article <b>may be <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Article_size" title="Wikipedia:Article size">too long</a> to read and navigate comfortably</b>.<span class="hide-when-compact"> Consider <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Splitting" title="Wikipedia:Splitting">splitting</a> content into sub-articles, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Summary_style" title="Wikipedia:Summary style">condensing</a> it, or adding <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Section#Subsections" title="Help:Section">subheadings</a>. Please discuss this issue on the article's <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk:List_of_subnational_entities_by_Human_Development_Index" title="Talk:List of subnational entities by Human Development Index">talk page</a>.</span></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1251242444"><table class="box-Dablinks plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-move" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td class="mbox-image"><div class="mbox-image-div"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Disambig.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="List%20of%20subnational%20entities%20by%20Human%20Development%20Index%20-%20Wikipedia_files/Disambig.svg_003.png" decoding="async" width="40" height="32" class="mw-file-element" srcset="List%20of%20subnational%20entities%20by%20Human%20Development%20Index%20-%20Wikipedia_files/Disambig.svg.png 1.5x, List%20of%20subnational%20entities%20by%20Human%20Development%20Index%20-%20Wikipedia_files/Disambig.svg_002.png 2x" data-file-width="230" data-file-height="183"></a></span></div></td><td class="mbox-text"><div class="mbox-text-span">This article <b>currently <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Disambiguation_pages_with_links" title="Wikipedia:Disambiguation pages with links">links</a> to a large number of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Disambiguation" title="Help:Disambiguation">disambiguation pages</a> (or back to itself)</b>.<span class="hide-when-compact"> Please <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Piped_link" title="Wikipedia:Piped link">help direct</a> these ambiguous links to articles dealing with the specific meaning intended. <small>Read the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Dablinks/FAQ" title="Template:Dablinks/FAQ">FAQ</a></small>.</span>  <span class="date-container"><i>(<span class="date">March 2025</span>)</i></span></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>The following list shows the subnational entities and regions included in the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_Development_Index" title="Human Development Index">Human Development Index</a> report, sorted by their score. The HDI is a summary measure of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_development_(economics)" title="Human development (economics)">human development</a>
 that considers three dimensions: health, education, and standard of 
living. It is calculated by taking the geometric mean of three 
normalized indicators: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Life_expectancy" title="Life expectancy">life expectancy</a> at birth, mean and expected <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Education" title="Education">years of schooling</a>, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gross_national_income" title="Gross national income">gross national income per capita</a>.
 The HDI ranges from 0 to 1, with higher values indicating higher human 
development. The HDI itself was created by Pakistani economist <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahbub_ul_Haq" title="Mahbub ul Haq">Mahbub ul Haq</a> in 1990, and was further used by the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UNDP" class="mw-redirect" title="UNDP">UNDP</a>
 to measure the country's development in its annual Human Development 
Reports.The index was initially calculated at the country level. The 
Global Data Lab at <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radboud_University_Nijmegen" title="Radboud University Nijmegen">Radboud University</a>
 in the Netherlands launched a subnational HDI (SHDI) in 2018, which 
covers around 1,800 regions in over 160 countries to better reflect the 
differences within countries.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
 Global Data Lab also provides the Subnational Human the Subnational 
Gender Development Index (SGDI) and data on income, years of education 
and life expectancy on the subnational level. The SHDI and SGDI are 
based on the UNDP's official HDI and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gender_Development_Index" title="Gender Development Index">GDI</a>, but they use subnational data in addition to national data.
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="List">List</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=List_of_subnational_entities_by_Human_Development_Index&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: List"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Based on the Human Development Index report,<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span class="cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class="cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> as compiled by the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations_Development_Programme" title="United Nations Development Programme">United Nations Development Programme</a> (UNDP), which does not include <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/States_with_limited_recognition" class="mw-redirect" title="States with limited recognition">states with limited recognition</a> who are non-<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UN_Member_States" class="mw-redirect" title="UN Member States">UN Member States</a>.
</p>
